Understanding "business formal" versus "business professional" is key. Formal is stricter, often requiring a full suit, while professional allows for more flexibility in separates.
Pay attention to footwear requirements for different dress codes. Heels, dress shoes, or smart loafers are often necessary, not just sneakers.
