I always use my smartphone to pay at the self-checkout machines because contactless payment is incredibly fast and I do not have to carry my physical wallet.
I always prefer using the self-checkout lanes because they are usually faster when I only have a few items in my basket. I just need to scan my loyalty card first.
An unexpected item was detected in the bagging area, and now the screen is completely frozen. I will have to wait for the store assistant to come and reset it.
