Because he missed his flight, he arrived late. If he had left earlier, he would have caught it. Therefore, planning ahead is vital for travel.
Because all birds have wings, and a robin is a bird, it follows that a robin has wings. If it didn't, it wouldn't be classified as a bird.
Because the ice cream is melting, it must be warm in the room. If it were cold, it would remain solid. Therefore, melting implies heat.
Because he missed the train, he will be late for the meeting. If he had left earlier, he would have caught it. Therefore, punctuality requires planning.
The dog is barking excitedly. Therefore, someone must be at the door. If we hear a knock, that's further proof. Because he always barks at visitors, it's reliable.
The streetlights just came on. Therefore, it's getting dark outside. If we look out the window, we'll see the dim light. Because evening approaches, this is normal.
The milk smells sour. Therefore, it is likely spoiled. If it tastes bad, then we absolutely shouldn't drink it. Because it's past its date, this is expected.
The car is making a strange rattling noise. Therefore, there might be a mechanical problem. If the check engine light is on, get it inspected. Because it's getting worse, don't delay.
There are muddy footprints leading into the house. Therefore, someone came in with dirty shoes. Because the dog was just outside, it's probably his doing.
