Always rinse your mouth with water after you finish flossing. This helps to wash away any loose plaque and debris that you have successfully dislodged from between your teeth today.
If your gums bleed slightly when you start flossing, do not stop. Continue the habit gently, and the bleeding will likely decrease as your gum tissue becomes healthier over time.
