Records show that my great-great-grandfather migrated from Lebanon to Argentina. Like many Syrian-Lebanese immigrants of his time, he started working as a peddler before opening his own shop.
My grandmother had to work in a sweatshop under terrible conditions for very low pay. Despite the exhaustion, she saved every penny to send back to her parents in Italy.
When the war broke out, my grandparents had to flee overnight with nothing but the clothes on their backs. Their survival story is a testament to human resilience and hope.
