My grandmother taught me how to bake bread from scratch, emphasizing the importance of kneading the dough with love. That kitchen became a sanctuary of shared stories and laughter.
We celebrate the birth of each new family member by sewing a personalized patch onto a large family quilt, which tells the story of our lineage through vibrant colors and fabrics.
