Excuse me, if you are looking for a pharmacy, there is one open twenty-four hours a day just two blocks down this street on your right-hand side.
Excuse me, but you might want to move your car to the other side of the street. They do street sweeping on this side on Thursdays, and you could get fined.
Excuse me, but you might want to put your phone in your front pocket while walking through this busy market. It is quite easy for things to slip out unnoticed.
Excuse me, but you might want to buy a daily transit pass instead of single tickets. It will save you a lot of money if you plan to travel much.
That sounds like a wonderful idea for a vacation, but I have already booked my flights and accommodation for a quiet trip to the countryside instead. Thanks anyway!
I understand your concern about my work hours, but I am currently finishing a major project and things will definitely quiet down once we launch next month. Thanks anyway!
You have been the strong one for so long, and it is okay to break down. I suggest letting your tears flow and letting someone else take care of you today.
I know you feel guilty about taking time for yourself, but you cannot pour from an empty cup. I strongly advise you to prioritize your self-care without any regrets.
He is shivering and his teeth are chattering despite wearing a thick winter coat. He must be freezing. It can't be warm outside even though the sun is shining brightly.
Her purse and keys are on the kitchen counter, but she is nowhere to be seen. She must be in the backyard. She can't have gone far without her personal belongings.
The store window is shattered and there are police cars parked outside with flashing lights. There must have been a robbery. It can't be a simple accident.
He is wearing a very expensive suit and driving a brand new luxury sports car. He must be very wealthy. He might be the CEO of a successful company.
Her suitcase is packed and sitting by the front door next to her passport. She must be going on a trip. She might be flying to Europe tonight.
The dog is barking loudly at the fence. There must be a stranger outside, or it might just be the neighbor's cat walking along the top of the wall.
He has a lot of keys on his ring. He must manage a large building, or he might just be someone who never throws away old, useless keys.
Her car is not in the driveway and her phone goes straight to voicemail. She must be driving home right now, though she might be stuck in heavy traffic.
The grass is completely wet this morning. It can't be from the sprinklers because they are broken. It must have rained heavily overnight, or perhaps the morning dew was exceptionally heavy.
The pavement is wet but all the parked cars are dry. It can't have rained recently. The street sweeper must have passed by, or a water main might have burst down the road.
The kitchen smells strongly of burnt toast, but nobody is cooking right now. It can't be the toaster because it's unplugged. Someone might be playing a prank on us.
The street is completely blocked by police cars and flashing lights. There must be a serious accident ahead, or it might be a planned road construction that we forgot about.
The front door is unlocked and wide open, but nothing seems to be missing. My roommate must be nearby, or he might be just taking out the garbage downstairs.
The milk in the refrigerator tastes extremely sour today. It can't be expired because the date is fine. The fridge must be broken and not keeping things cold enough.
The computer screen suddenly went black and won't turn back on. It can't be a dead battery because it is plugged in. The power cord must be damaged, or the screen might be dead.
The dog is barking at the front door. There must be someone outside, or perhaps he heard a stray cat. He can't be barking at nothing at this hour.
There are muddy footprints in the hallway. Someone must have come inside without wiping their shoes, or perhaps the dog snuck in. It can't be from me, surely.
He bought a brand new luxury sports car. He must have won the lottery, or perhaps he got that big promotion at his company recently, I guess.
The alarm didn't go off when the vault was opened last night. The thief must have known the security code, or the system might have been disabled beforehand.
John is pacing up and down the hallway before his big job interview. He must be feeling terribly nervous, though he might also be excited about this new career opportunity.
There is a giant package waiting on our doorstep with fragile stickers all over. It must be the new television. It can't be the small book I ordered.
The glass on the kitchen floor is shattered into pieces. The cat could have knocked it off the counter, or the wind might have blown it down.
He thinks he lost his wallet at the movie theater last night. It might be in the lost and found, but I am not very optimistic about finding it there.
The weather forecast predicts a perfectly sunny weekend. It might stay clear, but the wind is picking up, so I am a little skeptical about their prediction this time.
They suggested that we take the scenic route along the coast. It might be beautiful, but I am not sure if we have enough petrol to make the detour safely.
He told me he would return the borrowed book by Friday morning. He might remember, but he is notoriously forgetful, so I am not holding my breath for it.
The dog is barking at the front door constantly. There might be someone outside, but it could also just be a dry leaf blowing across the porch in the wind.
I see a set of keys on the kitchen counter, but John just left with his car. Those can't be his keys because he wouldn't be able to drive away without them.
The signature on this check is written in very elegant cursive handwriting with blue ink. It can't be Sarah's signature because she always signs her name in block letters using black pen.
The recipe specifically calls for fresh, sweet strawberries to make the dessert taste right. This bitter fruit in the bowl can't be a strawberry; it looks and tastes more like a cranberry.
The package delivered today is extremely light and rattles when I shake it gently. It can't be the heavy iron skillet that I ordered online last week because that weighs five pounds.
Your phone has been ringing in your backpack this entire afternoon. It can't be lost in the park like you thought; you just didn't hear it because of the noise.
The cat is sleeping peacefully on my lap and hasn't moved for hours. That scratching sound in the attic can't be her; there must be a mouse up there.
There is a brand new car parked in their driveway. They must have won the lottery recently or received a very generous inheritance from a wealthy distant relative.
I found a set of keys on the dining room table. One of our dinner guests might have dropped them while they were leaving the house last night.
The window is shattered and there is a brick lying on the living room rug. Someone must have thrown it through the glass during the middle of the night.
He arrived at the party wearing a very wet jacket and holding a broken umbrella. It must have started pouring rain just as he was walking over here.
The store is completely dark and the metal security gate is pulled down tight. They must have closed early today because of the holiday weekend.
The kitchen smells amazing and there is a warm chocolate cake sitting on the counter. My mother must have baked it today, or my sister might be practicing her baking.
He is wearing a very expensive suit, a luxury watch, and driving a brand new sports car. He must be extremely wealthy, or he might just be renting them for today.
He is rubbing his temples and squinting his eyes at the bright screen of his laptop. He must have a terrible headache, or he might need to get new glasses.
She is wearing a beautiful diamond ring on her left hand. She must have gotten engaged recently. It might be a family heirloom, but it looks brand new.
The sky has turned extremely dark and the wind is blowing fiercely. A huge storm must be coming our way. It might start pouring down in any minute now.
I hear some strange scratching noises coming from the attic. It must be squirrels nesting up there. It might also be the old tree branches scraping against the roof.
The car engine is making a loud, metallic clanking sound. There must be something seriously wrong with the motor. It might be dangerous to drive it right now.
He didn't study for the exam at all and fell asleep halfway through it. He can't have passed the test, but there might be a small chance he guessed right.
The security guard walks past our window at exactly fifteen minutes past the hour. This strict routine must be mandated by the company. It can't be a random patrol.
The pattern of footprints in the snow shows deep heel strikes. The person must be running very fast. They can't be walking casually, but they might be carrying heavy loads.
The grid pattern has a missing tile in the bottom right corner. The replacement piece must be a blue hexagon. It can't be a red circle, but it might be green.
The financial charts indicate a head-and-shoulders pattern forming on the daily index. This must be a bearish reversal signal. It can't be a bullish breakout, though it might fail.
This milk smells really sour and looks a bit clumpy. It must be expired. You can't drink it because it might make you very sick.
She looks incredibly pale and is shivering despite the warm weather. She must be feeling ill. She might have caught a cold yesterday.
The car engine is making a terrible rattling sound. Something must be wrong with the motor. It can't be safe to drive it today.
He has bought a brand new luxury sports car. He must have won the lottery. He can't be poor anymore with that kind of money.
He didn't eat anything at the buffet and only drank water. He can't be very hungry today, or he might have an upset stomach that is making him feel unwell.
The price of this designer handbag is incredibly low on this website. It can't be authentic at that price. It must be a fake copy from an unauthorized seller.
The car engine is making a terrible rattling sound and smoke is coming from the hood. It must be overheating. It can't be safe to drive any further.
He is wearing a very expensive watch and driving a brand new sports car. He must have a high-paying job. He might be the owner of that company.
The milk in the refrigerator has a sour smell and has turned thick. It must have expired already. It can't be safe to drink it with breakfast.
He is shivering violently and his teeth are chattering while he wraps his arms around himself. He must be freezing cold. He can't be comfortable in that thin summer t-shirt.
The store has a massive sign that says "Everything Must Go" with huge discounts on all items. They must be closing down permanently. They can't be making a profit anymore.
There is a long line of cars stretched out for miles and nobody is moving at all. There must be a major accident ahead. It might take hours to clear.
Her suitcase is fully packed by the door and her passport is lying on the kitchen counter. She must be going on a trip. She might be leaving today.
He has a giant smile on his face and is jumping up and down with joy. He must have passed his difficult exam. He might have gotten a perfect score, but he can't be disappointed.
If she doesn't practice her presentation tonight, she might forget her lines tomorrow. That must be embarrassing, and the board of directors can't be easily impressed by a messy speech.
The car engine is making a terrible rattling noise and smoke is pouring out. It can't be simple wear and tear, so might the mechanic have made a mistake?
He didn't recognize his own sister when she walked into the room. He must be suffering from severe memory loss, or he might just be playing a cruel joke.
Why is the boss suddenly being so nice to everyone in the office? She must be planning to announce some lay-offs, or she might have received a big promotion.
